The paper discusses the technical evaluation of smartphone apps that offer anonymity, ephemerality, and end-to-end encryption. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as the paper examines the security properties of these apps. Additionally, the paper uses static and dynamic analysis to evaluate the apps, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the features and promises of these apps, which could fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and programming languages (cs.PL).
